"a.不妥协的 【英】 adj. 不妥协的(uncompromi sing) 【考】 firm : intransigent / concerned : obsessed(坚定过分是顽固/关 心过分是沉迷)intransigent : acquiesce / deferential : offend(不妥协的不会默许/ 尊敬的不会冒犯)反义词：open to compromise(寻求和解 的); tractable(易管教的) 【记】 in(不)+transigent( 妥协的) adj. 极端不妥协的 = uncompromising 【记】transigent(adj 妥协的)trans交换, gen产生, t它(合同): 通过交换产生合同－因为妥协了. 参: transfer(v 转移) 【类】firm: intransigent = concerned: obsessed坚定过分是不妥协的 = 关心过分是沉迷的intransigent: acquiesce = deferential: offend不妥协的不会默许 = 尊敬的不会冒犯 【反】open to compromise(寻求和解); tractable(adj 易驾驭的) 【记】in不 + transact 办理，交易，谈判→不作交易→不谈判不妥协；transigent 可看作transact的变体 【相关】transient 短暂的, 瞬时的 intransigent (adj.)  1881, from French intransigeant, from Spanish los intransigentes, literally ""those not coming to agreement,"" name for extreme republican party in the Spanish Cortes 1873-4, from in- ""not"" (see in- (1)) + transigente ""compromising,"" from Latin transigentem (nominative transigens), present participle of transigere ""come to an agreement, accomplish, to carry through"" (see transaction). Acquired its generalized sense in French."
